column2: TL;DR: I think ETH passes the Howey Test.   ICO + mining = common enterprise
Unless people build things to work on ETH  the downward market pressure of mined coins eventually pushes the price towards zero.
ETH  itself  does not pass the #Bitcoin Test:  It held an ICO w/o distributing all tokens  therefore monetized later mining artificially.
